President Donald J. Trump intends to nominate Scott Hutchins for the position of Under Secretary of Agriculture for Research, Education, and Economics at the Department of Agriculture. Hutchins currently works as the global leader of integrated field sciences for Corteva Agriscience and is an adjunct professor at the University of Nebraska. He previously served as president of the Entomological Society of America and has degrees in entomology from Auburn University, Mississippi State University, and Iowa State University.